ge of temperatures (14.5\u201337\u00b0C), but often at &lt;20\u00b0C. Humidity in roosts was highly variable for most species and we did not detect any trend regarding this factor. Our data suggest that the thermoregulatory ability resulting from the complex interaction of body size, type of food, and taxonomic affiliation constrains species with respect to types of roosts that they can successfully exploit. Our results support the hypothesis that temperature is the most important physical factor influencing roost selection in bats.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Avila-Flores, Rafael", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Medell\u00edn, Rodrigo A.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/dcb10c4808f277572f80d75021441829", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/e5bae27d65b8c170a067d531d9423ec0f879a1b2738d0a0432bcf65ba915017e", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/5DBSY7B4", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/5DBSY7B4", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/3a068b983ee0b1de85603e497473676a!/b314240-317415", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "4", "pages": "675-687", "title": "Journal of Mammalogy", "volume": "85"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{